Q. How do you feel about carrying on his legacy, carrying his name, literally?  You talk to so many people and they remember him as a wonderful person.  How gratifying is it to come and honor him?
ORLANDO BROWN: It's been very important, man, you know what I mean?  I'm Brown, Junior, so I understand the responsibility that it comes with and I understand it's a privilege at the same time, man, and I'm hoping to continue to get better and reach the goals that I set, you know what I mean, that we both set.  I reached the goals that he set and couldn't reach.  So, yeah, man, I got a lot, man, that's why I play with a big chip on my shoulder for my mom and I'm continuing to carry on the legacy and make sure I reach the goals that I set.
